title: For Sale/Trade:  Scoped Ruger .22/45.
postcontent:
The gun itself is self explanatory from the pictures. Target model. All information will be found as you research the firearm. 2x10 round magazines.

Though mine is a tad different from most. I have a relatively inexpensive 2-7 scout scope mounted on mine, and it has served incredibly well due to the light recoil of .22. Holds zero well, even if the scope is removed and put back. I'm able to hit quarter sized groups at 25 yards, a rest, and quality ammo. Will come with the single point sling that's mounted securely on the ring stud, since holsters for scoped pistols are hard to find/pricy.

At some point in time, I realized that I didn't need to carry "The Survival Rifle" of some semi-auto .22 rifle. Even take down models are bulkier than even a scoped pistol, and that's without the rifle having a scope. Unless you're a horrible stalker, anyone can get within 50 yards of small game, and that's easily scoped pistol range. No need to carry something that I don't need. 
But that's just my thought process.


I'm moving to a state that requires firearms to be registered, and I figured that I can live without this one while I'm there.
Thanks for your time.
